properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 9 at 2:48PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a Gale Watch,
which is in effect from late Friday night through late Saturday
night.

* WINDS...South gales to 35 kt this evening. Northeast gales to 40
kt, with a few gusts to 45 kt possible late Friday night
through Saturday evening.

* SIGNIFICANT WAVES...to 7 ft this evening. To 16 ft late Friday
night through Saturday evening.

* OCCASIONAL WAVES...to 9 ft this evening. To 21 ft late Friday
night through Saturday evening.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased...but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE FRIDAY NIGHT THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
